# Python Coding Standards

## Code Style
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Include inline comments explaining complex logic
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use type hints where appropriate

## Virtual Environment
- Always run Python code in virtual environment (.venv or venv)
- Use `source .venv/bin/activate` before running Python scripts

## Error Handling
- Include proper error handling with try-catch blocks
- Use logging for informative error messages
- Validate required parameters before processing

## Databricks Integration
- Use environment variables for sensitive credentials
- Implement graceful fallbacks when Databricks connector is not available
- Include proper connection error handling